  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" State Represented By Inspector of Police, CBI, ACB, Visakhapatnam versus Eluri Srinivasa Chakravarthi and Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_5_988_1006','2025INSC758'); ><font size='4'> <strong>STATE REPRESENTED BY INSPECTOR OF POLICE, CBI, ACB, VISAKHAPATNAM<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>ELURI SRINIVASA CHAKRAVARTHI AND OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 988</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 758</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005742025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PANKAJ MITHAL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SARASA VENKATANARAYANA BHATTI</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the two letters could have been looked at or relied upon by the Special Court for exercising its jurisdiction u/s.239, Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; &ndash; Material to be relied upon &ndash; FIR registered by CBI, charges filed u/ss.120B r/w. 420, 468, 471, IPC and s.13(2) r/w 13(1)(d), PC Act alleging that the accused conspired to purchase cotton at lower prices, hoarded these cotton stocks and resold it to Cotton Corporation of India<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 22-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2784-2794/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_5_988_1006','2